Delegate @HalaAyala—a former cybersecurity analyst—has been active in the Prince William County community for more than three decades, and is bringing that experience to Richmond to focus on improving healthcare, education, transportation, and women's rights.

Clinton Jenkins was born and raised in Virginia's 76th district before enlisting in the Army. Now, he operates a local real estate company in Suffolk, and understands first-hand the needs and concerns of the community.

West Point graduate and Army veteran Dan @HelmerVA is running to represent HD 40. His priorities include protecting our children from gun violence, improving transportation, ending the corruption in Virginia politics, and protecting women's reproductive rights.

.@DelegateFowler, also running in Virginia Beach, is a dedicated community leader whose home reno business helps military families. In her time in the House of Delegates, she has advocated for affordable healthcare, pay raises for teachers, and climate change prevention.

Navy Veteran @MissyforSenate, running in Virginia Beach, is working for increased education funding, gun violence prevention, and environmental sustainability, among other issues. She is endorsed by both President Obama and Vice President Biden.
